It was a case of taxi meets tree when the driver of a Toyota Quantum allegedly lost control of his vehicle and slammed into a tree, in Phoenix, on Sunday. The driver sustained injuries in the crash and fortunately, there were no occupants in the taxi. The Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) Phoenix Operations Centre received a call from a passerby at 10.14am reporting the accident.
Prem Balram, head of Rusa said that on arrival, it was established that the taxi was overtaking a vehicle when the driver lost control of his vehicle and ploughed into a tree. “The driver was the only occupant of the mini bus at the time of the accident. He was treated for his injuries on scene before being transported to hospital by ambulance,” Balram said.